column5: Just wondering how many fishing boards people are on other than OFC. I'm mostly on OFC but I also use Spoonpullers, myccr and Algonquin Adventures.
Regularly, I visit just a couple all season long.  During Ice fishing I stalk three boards.  Otherwise,  I visit about 10 others on occasion - mostly US state fishing boards, like MI, MN and OH.

OFC, OFF, KA, NA, Hipwader, Floatboard, Fly tying forum, Classic fly tying forum, Ultralight fly fishing,  Fibreglass fly rodders, Speyclave, Ice shanty, Spoonpullers (only joined to sell a reel though), and I might be on the simcoe board, can't remember if I signed up.
This one obviously and ohio game fishing. Steelheadphycho on both. I probably spend 10 times more time on this one than that one.
Spoonpullers, NFN, Lake Ontario United, Great Lakes Angler, Walleye Central, Stomps 68,
Im on a few, same name everywhere. Spend the most time between this one and one other.  S.
OFC and NOFF (Northern Ontario Fishing Forum)
